.dmirs-cache/

# DR drill backup artefacts (regeneratable; one JSON per drill run).
# The dated drill RESULT lives in internal/DR-RESTORE-DRILL-*.md (committed);
# the raw row dumps here are ephemeral evidence, recreated by `npm run dr:audit-drill`.
reports/dr-drills/

# Terraform — NEVER commit the provider cache or state.
#   .terraform/      — downloaded provider plugins + module cache (100s of MB).
#   *.tfstate*       — STATE: contains secrets (DB password, generated RA_AUTH_SECRET)
#                      in PLAINTEXT; lives in the remote S3+KMS backend, never in git.
#   *.tfvars         — real values incl. domain/zone/secrets. The committed template is
#                      terraform.tfvars.example (NOT matched by *.tfvars, so it stays).
# DO commit: .terraform.lock.hcl (pins provider versions/hashes for reproducibility).
**/.terraform/*
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
*.tfvars
*.auto.tfvars
crash.log
crash.*.log
override.tf
override.tf.json
*_override.tf
*_override.tf.json
